<center><h1>What makes a good dictator?</h1>
<h2>Learning about dictators</h2></center>
<h3>Adolf Hitler:</h3>
<h4>Hitler was an evil man. Characteristics of Hitler are powerful, violent and rude. He was powerful because he was
  the dictator of Germany and could do whatever he wanted because his people were at the mercy of him. He was violent
  in his everyday life, he was usually violent. Whether it was the people of his country, his country or other countries
  he was mean or violent to, he was usually violent to someone. He was also rude. A great example of this is when he
  went after the Jews to kill them. This was rude because they are just people who didn't do anything wrong other
  than upset Hitler in someway. There were a few things that led Hitler to come to power. One of them was he hated
  the Treaty of Versailles because it made Germnany look weak and he didn't like his country or himself looking
  weak. Hitler joined the party in 1919 which could have lead him to want to take over Germany. Hitler earned an
  iron cross which made him confident in himself. He then started the 25 point program which started him on the
  right path to becoming a dictator. As we know, he was terribly mean to the Jews and attempted to sieze power in
  Bavaria, but managed instead, to take power in other countries. Hitler wanted Germany to be superior. He didn't
  want Germany to falter and be embarrassed again like they were at the end of the first world war. He was embarrassed
  and disappointed in Germany's performance in WWI so he wanted to take over so that it didn't happen again.</h4>
<h3>Joseph Stalin:</h3>
  <h4>Stalin was a ruthless, trusting and intelligent negotiator. He was a communist who was somewhat trusting and
    he was very cruel. He was an intelligent and ruthless person who didn't like excuses. Soemthings that helped
    him rise to power is when he was young, he was run over by a car and that disformed his left arm so it was
    shorter than his right. People then made fun of him because of his disformed arm. His mother wanted him
    to become a priest, but he didn't want to pursue that, so he became a dictator. Someone exposed him to
    socialism and he was a communist after reading <i>Communist Manifesto</i>. He was also a great negotiator.
    He was incredibly ruthless in his attacks on other countries or people and he tried to bargin from a good
    position. That is why he always traded from a good stance. At first, he liked Hitler and they got along,
    but after the war, Stalin hated Hitler, but still wanted to trust him. Stalin was a good negotiator, so that's why he could bargin from
    a good position. Stalin had both socialist and communist beliefs. He started building a power base right
    away. He was high in the ranks after Lenin died, so he took power. Stalin took control of the Soviet Union.
    He killed and exiled members.</h4>
<h3>Benito Mussolini:</h3>
  <h4> Mussolini likes terrorizing people. He was bald most of his life. A trait that Mussolini had was he could
    charm people into liking him, but in the end, those same people would end up being the ones that threw him
    out of power and the ones that killed him. Some of the things that led him to take power was he had support
    in Italy's entry into WWI which is why he was drafted into Italy's army. Before that, he was a journalist
    in the socailist press. His father was a blacksmith and that is what his father wanted him to do, but that
    wasn't what was in store for him. Some traits he had as a dictator is that he terrorized his political
    opponents. He had a dream of re-establishing Italy and he had a plan to do so and he was enforcing his
    dream however he could.</h4>
<h3>Hideki Tojo</h3>
  <h4>Hideki Tojo was a dictator that had full power and he thought he could get as much power as he needed
    so he could be the chief and dictator. He came from an imperial background in his family. When Hirohito's father
    passed away, he became emperor of Japan. So Hirohito was the emperor of Japan or the God of Japan. He is worshiped
    like a god. If something is said by him, then the people will do it without thinking twice. Hideki is a military
    general and dictator. He ran the country off of what Hideki THOUGHT Hirohito wanted. He then slowly put himself
    in charge of the army, foreign affairs, education, commerce and the munitions industry.</h4>
<h3>Qualities dictators should have:</h3>
<h4>Every dictator should possess the qualities of having a clear plan for the country, persuading, and having the
  country’s best interests at heart because it empowers them to make good choices for their country, makes them popular
   and makes them more ruthless. </h4>
<h3>What led to the rise of dictators:</h3>
<h4>If people are unhappy with the government, then this will lead to a dictatorship because the country has a
  power gap and there is a ineffectual government and a lack of change.</h4>
