<h1> Warning!! Danger!! Dictators on the lose!</h1>
<h3>Dear the Recipient of this Letter,
  <br>
  <Br>
This letter is intended to warn you about an impending threat that the unaware stand no chance against: propaganda and dictators. Propaganda is information that portrays things that  are untrue or are made for the sake for winning the people over. Propaganda is usually targeted at certain people such as farmers, women, businessmen, children, and people of a certain religion. Dictators are usually the ones that put out the propaganda through someone else or by themselves. They usually put out the propaganda to influence someone to vote for or follow them. The reason you have no chance against dictators is because of how they rule. Dictators use their power to inflict fear among you. They can make you have fear by threatening you or someone you love. Another reason they are followed is because they seem like they know what they are doing and act like what they are doing is for the better of the people. The reason you don’t stand a chance against dictators and propaganda is because they are ruthless, undenyable and persuading.
<br>
<br>
	Dictators and propaganda are ruthless and they don’t care what happens to anyone else, as long as it means whatever they care about gets to the top. As seen with Adolf Hitler and Joseph Stalin how ruthless they were toward their enemy. For Hitler, his enemy was the Jews, for Stalin, anyone who disagreed with him. They also both had things they wanted to work for either their country, their people, their family or anyone/thing that they wanted to do well. As seen with Hitler, he wanted Germany to rise to power and to not be a disgrace like they were in first world war, so he took charge and changed the minds of the people so they could become more powerful. As for Stalin, he wanted the Soviet Union to do well. He turned a peaceful and sleeping country into a powerful and militaristic country. Both dictators mostly ruled by terror and many of their own people died during their dictatorship. To add on, because the dictators overviewed all the propaganda, the propaganda was also somewhat ruthless. As an example, when Hitler ruled, his propaganda showed the Jew’s doing all the bad and causing all Germany’s problems so that Hitler could get his people all on the same page that he was on. The reason the propaganda is also ruthless is because it is what the dictator believes. If the dictator believes that Jews are bad, that is what the propaganda is going to show, that Jews are bad and should not be trusted. If the dictator believes that their country is horrible and they need to improve, that is what the propaganda is going to be about. To add on to this, writing things that are mean and “ruthless” it is a lot easier than saying it to their face. As you can see, both dictators and propaganda is ruthless.
<br>
<br>
    Dictators and propaganda are undeniable because they use you feeling and choices against you, they will punish you if you if you choose not to listen, and they are very good at making it seem like they are the good guys. To start off, the propaganda they put in your head makes it seem like it was your decision when you have to make a choice about something. In class, Mr. Haydel made it seem like we were going to clap for Mya and when we didn’t, he tried to make us feel bad. This was a bit like
  propaganda because it messes with your feelings. Another reason people follow a dictator is because if they don’t, their punishment will be pretty bad if not death. Because dictators have so much power, they can really do anything they want to you. Lastly, they use propaganda to make it seem like they are the good guys. Dictators want to make you think that they are good, and anyone who is against them is bad. As you can see, Dictators use propaganda to make it seem like when you make a choice that it was your decision, they will punish you if you don’t listen, and they will make them look like the good guys to make you want to follow them.
<br><br>
  Finally, relating to the previous paragraph, dictators are quite persuasive. In history, Hitler was very persuasive because he, not only rose to power after dropping out of high school, but he managed to make a powerful country turn against a group of innocent people: the Jews. This takes some skill because, like all groups, they were mainly innocent, but also like all groups, there are some bad people that are Jews and he used those as a representation of all the Jews which isn’t accurate. Next, Joseph Stalin had his own methods of persuasion. He loved to bargain from a higher position, was ruthless in his attacks, and he had a plan so he started building a gigantic power base right away. Finally, Mussolini had his own tactics of persuasion. Like Hitler, he had a supposed “charm” and could use words to his will, and also like Hitler, he terrorized and threatened people. Overall, persuasion is a skill that all dictators need to have and have had in the past.
<br><br>
	Overall, you must heed our warning and ignore and distrust the propaganda that you are presented to: it may be difficult because you see propaganda a great deal more than you may think, but if you are careful, you can avoid the pull of propaganda. You just have to watch out for possible dictators and see if they’re actually doing what they are saying they’re doing and they’re not making any false promises. If you don’t, your country may be the next Holocaust Germany and a group, maybe your group, may be singled out and killed and hated by the rest of your country. You must also encourage others to do the same, as there is quite some power in the masses and stop reading anything that seems excessively biased and false, unless it is for entertainment purposes and will not cloud your opinions. If you do not do these things, we will all be an unwilling slave to an official’s darkest desires and everything that we do would be for them, and not for the people.

